    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\r\n\r\nKinda. `ch_open`, `sockconnect` alternative of Vim, has `close_cb`\r\n\r\n### Feature description\r\n\r\nI'd like to detect TCP disconnection to automatically reconnect. In short, I'd like to write Vim script code like\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nfunction! s:connect(address) abort\r\n  let l:chan = sockconnect('tcp', a:address, {\r\n        \\ 'rpc': v:true,\r\n        \\ 'on_close': { chan -> s:on_close(chan, a:address) },\r\n        \\})\r\n  \" ...\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\nfunction! s:on_close(chan, address) abort\r\n  echo \"Reconnect...\"\r\n  call s:connect(a:address)\r\nendfunction\r\n```\r\n\r\nOr is there any way to achive this functionality?\r\n\r\nComes from https://github.com/vim-denops/denops.vim/pull/206",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
